The paper deals with mutual information and its applications in communication complexity, which are topics that are typically covered in information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the information complexity of interactive protocols, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR), and the use of randomness in communication protocols, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
